OL,5, The process of hiring BBC chairman     
OL,6, Richard Sharp is to be reviewed by the 
OL,7, watchdog that oversees how public      
OL,8, appointments are made.                 
OL,10,FIt follows claims that shortly before  
OL,11,Fbeing given the job, Mr Sharp helped   
OL,12,Fthe then-prime minister, Boris Johnson,
OL,13,Fsecure a loan guarantee agreement.     
OL,15,FWilliam Shawcross, the Commissioner for
OL,16,FPublic Appointments, said the review   
OL,17,Fwould ensure the hiring followed rules.
OL,19,FMr Sharp said he "simply connected"    
OL,20,Fpeople and did not arrange financing.  
